The initial release of the NCmd library which makes it easier to write console based programs by providing the following features:
1) Provides the Cmd class to quickly create command line shell program. 2) Shell commands can be created using method naming conventions or method arguments. 3) A command line argument parser. 4) Live help 5) Auto command completion
Bug Fixes 1.0.1: 1) Fixed problem causing null reference exceptions when calling CmdLoop().
Bug Fixes 1.0.2: 1) Fixed bug in LineEditor class that caused expections with auto complete for commands of similar spelling.

FeedPackage.Description: NCache provides a cache provider for NHibernate and transforms its stand-alone InProc cache into a distributed cache. As you know, if your application is using NHibernate and running in a multi-server environment, the NHibernate stand-alone cache won't work because it does not synchronize the cache across multiple servers. However, NCache provides a distributed cache and fills in this need for NHibernate. NC-NHibernateCachingProvider requires NCache 4.4 to work.

FeedPackage.Description: Octopus Deploy is an automated deployment tool powered by NuGet. This tool adds a post-build activity to your Visual Studio project, so that an Octopus-compatible NuGet package is produced in the Bin directory whenever a Release build completes.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
This is an unofficial NuGet package of OctoPack from Octopus Deploy. This package was created to provide updates to OctoPack in a separate package because it seems that Octopus Deploy is no longer accepting pull request and has ceased making updates to the official package.
This package will follow the official updates and use the same version number using the revision number (4th digit) for additional enhancements. Any contributions from pull requests will also be reviewed and potentially accepted accordingly.
Contains the following enchancements: - Added MSBuild property to specify the output directory for newly created packages `/p:OctoPackOutDir=C:\ExampleOutputDir\`
FeedPackage.Summary: Build Octopus Deploy-compatible NuGet packages from your projects.
FeedPackage.Title: NCode.OctoPack
